      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so you're saying the intelligence/sophistication vibe usually leans towards East Asian or South Asian, while the crime/street vibe leans towards Latino or Black. why do you think those specific racial profiles are the most \"effective\" or \"realistic\" for those particular roles? like, what is it about those archetypes that makes them click for an audience in this genre?",
